1 Court of the county where the violation is alleged to have occurred; and
2 (b) Refer violations of this chapter to county attorneys, Commonwealth's
3 attorneys, and to the Attorney General.
4 (10) Nothing in this section shall be construed to prohibit an instructor, student,
5 cosmetologist, or nail technician from using callus graters for callus removal, and
6 the board shall not promulgate any administrative regulation prohibiting the use of
7 callus graters for callus removal.
8 (11) For the purposes of this chapter, any type of mobile salon shall be considered a
9 facility.
10 Section 3. KRS 317A.050 is amended to read as follows:
11 (1) All applicants for licensure under this chapter shall meet the following minimum
12 requirements:
13 (a) Be of good moral character and temperate habit;
14 (b) Be at least eighteen (18) years of age;
15 (c) Have a high school diploma, a High School Equivalency Diploma, or results
16 from the Test for Adult Basic Education indicating a score equivalent to the
17 twelfth grade of high school; and
18 (d) Have submitted the completed application along with the required license fee
19 as set forth in administrative regulation.
20 (2) Notwithstanding any provision to the contrary, the board may refuse to grant a
21 license to any applicant who fails to comply with the provisions of this chapter or
22 any administrative regulations promulgated by the board.
23 (3) The board shall issue a cosmetologist license to any person who:
24 (a) Has official certification from the state board or agency that certifies
25 cosmetology schools that the applicant has graduated from a licensed school
26 of cosmetology requiring one thousand five hundred (1,500) hours within five
27 (5) years of enrolling within the school; and
Page 8 of 17
XXXX 7/17/2025 3:53 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 215
1 (b) Has satisfactorily passed an examination prescribed by the board to determine
2 fitness to practice cosmetology.
3 (4) The board shall issue an esthetician license to any person who:
4 (a) Has satisfactorily completed seven hundred fifty (750) hours of instruction in
5 a licensed school approved by the board; and
6 (b) Has received a satisfactory grade on an examination prescribed by the board
7 to determine fitness to practice as an esthetician.
8 (5) The board shall issue a license to act as a nail technician to any person who:
9 (a) Has official certification from the state board or agency that certifies
10 cosmetology schools that the applicant has completed satisfactorily a nail
11 technician course of study of four hundred fifty (450) hours in a licensed
12 school of cosmetology within five (5) years of submitting an application for
13 licensure; and
14 (b) Has satisfactorily passed an examination prescribed by the board to determine
15 fitness to practice as a nail technician.
16 (6) The board shall issue a license to operate a salon, fixed or mobile, as follows:
17 (a) The board shall issue a license to operate a beauty salon to any licensed
18 cosmetologist. An owner who is not a licensed cosmetologist shall have a
19 licensed cosmetologist as manager of the beauty salon at all times. If the
20 owner, manager, or location of a beauty salon changes, the required form and
21 fee shall be submitted to the board.
22 (b) The board shall issue a license to operate an esthetic salon to any licensed
23 esthetician. An owner who is not a licensed esthetician shall have a licensed
24 esthetician or cosmetologist as manager of the esthetic salon at all times. If the
25 owner, manager, or location of an esthetic salon changes, the required form
26 and fee shall be submitted to the board.
27 (c) The board shall issue a license to operate a nail salon to any licensed nail
